<H3> <TI>   South's Opposition Urges Cancellation of Patriots </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK2002082994 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0819 GMT 20 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2002082994 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, February 20 (KCNA) -- The opposition 
Democratic Party of South Korea in a statement released by its 
spokesman Saturday urged the U.S. Government to drop the 
projected deployment of Patriot missiles in South Korea, which 
might provoke the North, a radio report from Seoul said. 
  The statement also demanded that the South Korean 
authorities 
pursue a self-determined diplomacy for the relaxation of the 
tensions on the Korean peninsula, said the radio. 

