<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> Japan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Takemura on Private Sector's Trade Efforts </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW2002142594 Tokyo MAINICHI SHIMBUN in Japanese 20 Feb 94 
Morning Edition p 2 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW2002142594 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo MAINICHI SHIMBUN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Japanese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Chief Cabinet Secretary Masayoshi Takemura, in a 19 
February speech in Nagoya, touched on the issue of Japan's trade 
surplus which has caused confrontation between Japan and the 
United States. He said: "The government is not in a position 
of being able to interfere in automakers' business in a 
capitalist nation or a country in which market mechanism 
functions well. And, there is no such law. If the automobile 
and insurance industries come up with ideas to solve the issue, 
it may be necessary for the government to support them in 
implementing the ideas." Thus, he indicated that trade 
imbalance should be corrected mainly through the private 
sector's voluntary efforts. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

