<H3> <TI>   Sakigake, JNP Qualify Support for Reshuffle </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW1902000594 Tokyo NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN in Japanese 17 Feb 
94 Evening Edition p 3 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW1902000594 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Japanese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] On the morning of 17 February, Shinto Sakigake 
[Harbinger] and the Japan New Party [JNP] held a staff meeting 
of Toitsukaiha, their joint floor group in the lower house, and 
exchanged views on the question of a possible cabinet reshuffle. 
As a result, they agreed on the following: 1) They will 
support the Hosokawa administration qualitatively; 2) the two 
parties will continue to cooperate in the lower house by 
maintaining the joint floor group; and 3) Diet members of the 
two parties will further solidify their ties. 
  Following the meeting, a senior Sakigake member explained: 
"Supporting the Hosokawa administration qualitatively means that 
we will support it even if Chief Cabinet Secretary Masayoshi 
Takemura is assigned to another post in the cabinet reshuffle." 
Thus, he indicated Sakigake would accept a cabinet reshuffle if 
it means Takemura is not ousted and remains in the cabinet. 

</TEXT>

