<H3> <TI>   LDP Official Criticizes Deregulation Plan </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW2102144594 Tokyo SANKEI SHIMBUN in Japanese 21 Feb 94 
Morning Edition p 2 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW2102144594 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo SANKEI SHIMBUN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Japanese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] On 19 February, Ryutaro Hashimoto, chairman of the 
Liberal Democratic Party's [LDP] Policy Research Council, spoke 
about the government's deregulation plan. 
  He said: "It is said there are 1,591 items listed, but there 
is a hitch to it. Deregulation will be implemented on only 231 
of these items by the end of fiscal year 1994, and only in 42 
cases will regulations be completely abolished." 
  Hashimoto made the remarks during a lecture he gave at a 
seminar for senior officials of the LDP's Miyazaki Prefectural 
Chapter. 
  He also criticized the government's attitude. 
  He said: "As such a large figure has been announced, Japan 
will face difficulties when the rest of the world becomes aware 
of the fact." 

