  [Text] Tokyo, Feb. 23 KYODO -- A senior Postal Ministry 
official may be forced to resign for comments on government 
policy toward high-definition television (HDTV) development, a 
Japanese broadcasting network executive said Wednesday [23 
February]. 
  The executive for a private broadcasting company asked to 
remain anonymous. 
  Akimasa Egawa, director general of the Broadcasting 
