<F P=100> Cambodia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Information Official on Anlung Veng `Mop Up' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK2402074894 Phnom Penh National Radio of Cambodia Network 
in Cambodian 0400 GMT 24 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2402074894 </F>
<F P=104>  Phnom Penh National Radio of Cambodia Network 
in Cambodian 0400 GMT 24 Feb 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Cambodian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] His Excellency [H.E.] Sieng Lapresse, adviser to 
the minister of information and chief of the Information 
Ministry cabinet, gave a news conference on 23 February to 
national and international reporters on the military situation 
in the wake of the capture by the Khmer Royal Armed Forces 
[KRAF] of major Khmer Rouge bases at Anlung Veng and An Seh. He 
said the KRAF was continuing to mop up Khmer Rouge elements in 
areas 15 km around the Anlung Veng base and that the Armed 
Forces had seized 175 assorted firearms, 13 vehicles, 14 field 
radios, and two tanks of fuel. 
  H.E. Sieng Lapresse further said that at An Seh, the KRAF 
seized a significant quantity of war materiel, including 15 
DK-75 shells, 30 70-mm shells, six APL shells, 30 hand grenades, 
and 574 cases of cartridges for AK rifles. He also disclosed 
that during the fighting the KRAF killed 28 Khmer Rouge 
soldiers, captured three, forced 26 others to surrender, and 
seized 246 guns. 

</TEXT>

