<H3> <TI>   Foreign Parties Support Pyongyang Declaration </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK2302051794 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0502 GMT 23 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2302051794 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, February 23 (KCNA) -- The Pyongyang 
declaration "Let Us Defend and Advance the Cause of Socialism" 
was recently signed by the Socialist Progressive Party, the 
militant party for equality and struggle of Madagascar; the 
Renovation Movement; the Unionist Democratic Union and the 
Progressive Socialist Rally, of Tunisia; and the Communist Party 
of Canada (Marxist-Leninist). 
  The declaration was signed by 207 political parties as of 
February 15. 
  In April, 1992, many delegates of communist and workers' 
parties and other political parties aspiring after socialism 
from 70 countries adopted the historical Pyongyang declaration 
reflecting their steadfast will to defend and advance the cause 
of socialism. 
  The declaration, elucidating the secret of defending and 
advancing the cause of socialism, stresses the need for each 
party to firmly maintain independence. 

</TEXT>

