<H3> <TI>   Kim Chong-il Receives More Birthday Greetings </TI></H3>
<H4>   Zimbabwe Sends Gift </H4>
<F P=102> SK2302114294 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1020 GMT 23 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2302114294 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, February 23 (KCNA) -- The dear leader 
Comrade Kim Chong-il received a gift from Zimbabwe on the 
occasion of his birthday. 
  A gift-conveying ceremony took place in Harare, Zimbabwe on 
February 14. 
  Speaking at the ceremony, N.T. Mawema, member of the Central 
Committee and director of the Political and Cultural Department 
of the Zimbabwe African National Union-Patriotic Front and 
chairman of the Zimbabwean National Committee for the Study of 
the Chuche Idea, referred in detail to the history of the 
revolutionary activities of Comrade Kim Chong-il. 
  The chairman said: 
  Kim Chong-il, he is just socialist Korea. 
  It is under the leadership of the great general Comrade Kim 
Chong-il with literary and military accomplishments and with 
loyalty and filial piety that Korean-style socialism is 
imposingly rising in the east of the globe, throwing its rays 
all over the world. 
  According to his interpretation of the gift, the gift "bell" 
is symbolic of the sound of the bell of chuche calling mankind 
to the accomplishment of the cause of independence and the tiger 
inscribed in the "bell" represents the majestic appearance of 
the general making the imperialists and the renegades of 
socialism shudder. 
  The gift was conveyed to the DPRK ambassador to Zimbabwe. 

</TEXT>

