<H3> <TI>   Foreign Groups Give Plants to Kim Chong-il </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK2402043094 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0410 GMT 24 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2402043094 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, February 23 (KCNA) -- Plants which were 
gifted to the dear leader Comrade Kim Chong-il from different 
countries are growing at the international friendship greenhouse 
situated at the foot of Mt. Taesong in Pyongyang. 
  There are more than 1,800 kinds of plants sent by party and 
state leaders, political and public figures and progressive 
people of different countries from 1976 up to now. 
  Last year alone, hundreds of rare woody plants and herbs 
were 
sent here from China, Poland and other countries. 
  Growing at the greenhouse are Kimilsongia and Kimchongilia 
well known to the Korean people as well as the world people and 
other temperate and tropical plants such as hippophae 
rhamnoides, hemerocallis, platycerium bifrucatum c. chr., 
camellia japonica and rhododendron indicum sweet. 
  Herbal plants include psidium guajava and prunus mume var. 
alphandii and cassia occidentalis l. 
  Cassia occidentalis l. is a rare plant for elixir which was 
discovered by Dr. Keita Aduna, a public figure of Mali, covering 
a long distance of more than 6,000 kilometres on the birthday of 
dear Comrade Kim Chong-il. 

</TEXT>

