<H3> <TI>   Kim Chong-il Sends Birthday Table to Woman </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK2402104894 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1002 GMT 24 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2402104894 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, February 24 (KCNA) -- The dear leader 
Comrade Kim Chong-il sent a birthday table to Kim Kyu-chol, a 
centenarian in Sonpong-up, Sonpong County. 
  Upon receiving the birthday table imbued with loving care 
amid blessings of her family, relatives and villagers, the 
100-year-old woman said she had wholeheartedly felt through her 
life how good her country was. "Because the dear leader pursues 
good politics for the people, I have been able to live 100 years 
and enjoy happiness today," she said. 
  In the DPRK, the number of macrobians is on a steady 
increase 
under the popular policies of the state. 
  The average life expectancy at birth is 74.5 years in Korea. 

</TEXT>

