<DOCNO> FBIS3-29951 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "dreas037_c_94036" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-EAS-94-037 </AU>
Document Type:Daily Report 
<DATE1>  24 Feb 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Events Mark 30th Anniversary of Rural Theses </TI></H3>
<H4>   Postage Stamps Mark Anniversary </H4>
<F P=102> SK2302114094 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1028 GMT 23 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2302114094 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, February 23 (KCNA) -- Korea recently 
issued memorial postage stamps and postcards on the occasion of 
the 30th anniversary of the publication of "Theses on the 
Socialist Rural Question in Our Country", a famous work of the 
great leader President Kim Il-song. 
  Stamps carry a picture of President Kim Il-song looking with 
a bright smile on his face over fields of golden ears of rice 
ripe under the rays of the theses and a picture of the dear 
leader Comrade Kim Chong-il walking through crop fields with 
farmers. 
  Some stamps depict agricultural working people who are 
riding 
Chollima under the banner of the three revolutions, ideological, 
technical and cultural, and picture socialist cooperative fields 
where irrigation and electrification have been completed and 
mechanisation and extensive use of chemicals are being promoted 
powerfully. 
  There are stamps portraying agricultural working people who 
are being trained into agronomists and assistant agronomists and 
many other stamps showing the successful promotion of the 
ideological, technical and cultural revolutions in the 
countryside. 
  Postcards and envelopes reflect the validity and vitality of 
the socialist rural theses. 

</TEXT>

