<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Events Mark 30th Anniversary of Rural Theses </TI></H3>
<H4>   Art Exhibition Opens </H4>
<F P=102> SK2402053094 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0455 GMT 24 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2402053094 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, February 24 (KCNA) -- An art exhibition 
opened here Wednesday to mark the 30th anniversary of the 
publication of the rural theses. 
  On display are more than 70 art works of various forms 
including Korean paintings "The Great Leader Comrade Kim Il-song 
Conversing With Peasants To Open a New History of Agricultural 
Cooperativization," "The Dear Leader Comrade Kim Chong-il 
Transplanting Rice With Artistes" and "The Dear Leader Comrade 
Kim Chong-il Walking on a Farm Field in a Bountiful Year" 
representing the revolutionary activities of the great leader 
President Kim Il-song and the dear leader Comrade Kim Chong-il. 
  The works show the proud realities of the Korean countryside 
that has been turned into a modern socialist countryside good to 
live in under the wise guidance of President Kim Il-song and 
Comrade Kim Chong-il, the vigorous drive of agricultural working 
people who are carrying through the agriculture-first policy of 
the party and the working people actively helping the socialist 
rural communities. 
  An opening address was made by Chang Chol, vice-premier of 
the Administration Council and minister of culture and art. 

</TEXT>

