<F P=103> SK2402115494 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, Feb. 24 (YONHAP) -- The Woosung business 
group, a leading business conglomerate of South Korea, will 
build and operate an international school here in Beijing. 
Woosung will set up an international school of elementary and 
secondary school courses in a joint venture with the Beijing 
Joint Agriculture, Industry and Commerce Corp., a public firm 
controlled by the Beijing municipality. 
  A basic agreement on the school project was signed by the 
two 
partners in a brief ceremony here on Thursday. Ground is 
expected to be broken within the year for the construction of 
school facilities. Under the agreement, the two sides will 
equally invest 30 million dollars in the scheme. The school, 
capable of accommodating about 1,000 students, will be located 
at a 16,500-square-meter land in the Chaoyang Ward District in 
downtown Beijing. Choe Song-chin, vice group chairman, said here 
the two sides also agreed to build apartments, arcades and 
tennis courts around the school. 

