<F P=102>  SK2402080794 Seoul YONHAP in English 0722 GMT 24 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2402080794 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Seoul, Feb. 24 (YONHAP) -- Dacom Corp. will become 
the first Korean concern to participate in the local 
telecommunications business in Russia, Dacom officials said on 
Thursday. Dacom said that its subsidiary, Dacom International 
Corp., and Goldstar Information and Communications Ltd. will 
sign a contract with Russian firms to invest in "Nakhodka Free 
Economic Zone Telecommunications Co." on Friday in Seoul. 
Nakhodka City in Primoskiy Kray (maritime province) of Russia 
recently established the company to provide telecommunications 
service within the city. 
  Six Russian organizations including the Administrative 
Committee of Nakhodka Free Economic Zone, Nakhodka City and 
telecommunications and information agency of Primoskiy Kray will 
invest 2 million U.S. dollars while Dacom International and 
Goldstar plan to invest another 2 million dollars in the local 
telecommunications business. Dacom will pour about 1.8 million 
dollars and Goldstar 200,000 dollars into the joint venture. 
Nakhodka Free Economic Zone Telecommunications Co. will begin 
full operations in April and eventually expand its service to 
all areas of Primoskiy Kray, according to Dacom. 

</TEXT>

