<H3> <TI>   Nine SDP Join Korea-Japan Parliamentarian Union </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK2402030494 Seoul YONHAP in English 0237 GMT 24 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2402030494 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, Feb. 24 (YONHAP) -- Nine lawmakers from the 
Japanese Social Democratic Party [SDP], including former 
chairman Sadao Yamahana and current Policy Board Chairman 
Nobuyuki Sekiyama, have joined the South Korea-Japan 
Parliamentarians' Union, informed sources said on Wednesday. 
  The SDP had been hoping to join the union for a long time, 
but other members from the Liberal Democratic Party, Democratic 
Socialist Party and Komeito Party rejected it because the SDP 
attached importance to North Korea and refused to change its 
policy toward South Korea. The nine SDP lawmakers joined the 
union on a personal level and the SDP's membership on a party 
level is still not permitted. 
  Yamahana, who is now state minister in charge of political 
reform in the cabinet, visited South Korea last September for 
the first time as SDP chairman. 

</TEXT>

