<F P=100> Vietnam </F>
<H3> <TI>   VNA Reports ASEAN Secretary General's Activities </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK2302155494 Hanoi VNA in English 1500 GMT 23 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> BK2302155494 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi VNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Hanoi VNA Feb. 23 -- Secretary General of the ASEAN 
organization Datuk Ajit Singh and his wife arrived here on Feb. 
21 for a week-long official visit to Vietnam as guests of 
Foreign Minister Nguyen Manh Cam. 
  Mr. Datuk Ajit Singh was received here yesterday by Prime 
Minister Vo Van Kiet. 
  He held talks with Foreign Minister Nguyen Manh Cam. The two 
sides informed each other of the measures to promote the 
multi-sided cooperative relations between Vietnam and ASEAN in 
the spirit of the agreement reached by the two sides at the 26th 
ASEAN Foreign Ministers' Conference last July in Singapore. The 
ASEAN secretary general informed the Vietnamese chief diplomat 
of the ASEAN Standing Committee's decision to invite Vietnam to 
participate as observer in six professional cooperation 
committees and a number of cooperative projects of ASEAN in the 
fields of science, technology, culture, information, public 
health, environment, tourism and training. In order to increase 
information and mutual understanding, Mr. Datuk Ajit Singh 
added, ASEAN Secretariat will send its officials to Vietnam to 
exchange views with the Vietnamese side on concrete matters 
relating to ASEAN. 
  The ASEAN secretary general also exchanged views on 
Vietnam-ASEAN relations with representatives of various 
ministries, branches and research institutes. 
  Mr. Datuk Ajit Singh and his wife left here yesterday 
afternoon to visit Hue, Da Lat and Ho Chi Minh City. 

</TEXT>

