<F P=100> Vietnam </F>
<H3> <TI>   Phan Van Khai Satisfied With Japanese Aid </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK2402070894 Hanoi VNA in English 0606 GMT 24 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> BK2402070894 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi VNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Hanoi VNA Feb. 24 -- Vice Prime Minister Phan Van 
Khai received here yesterday Mr. Eisei Ito, vice minister of 
construction of Japan who is on a working visit to Vietnam. 
  Speaking to his guest, Vice Prime Minister Phan Van Khai 
expressed his satisfaction at the quick and fine development of 
the relations between Vietnam and Japan. Mr. Khai highly 
appreciated the official development aid (ODA) given by the 
Japanese Government to some Vietnamese key projects. He hailed 
the further promotion of cooperation between the two 
Construction Ministries. 
  For his part, Mr Ito expressed his pleasure at multi-faceted 
achievements recorded by the Vietnamese people in the present 
period of renovation. 
  Mr. Ito wished that the cooperation between the two 
Construction Ministries would be further promoted and an 
exchange of personnel would be implemented. 
  Also present at the reception were Vietnamese Vice Minister 
of Construction Pham Sy Liem and Japanese Ambassador to Vietnam 
Hiroyuki Yushita. 

</TEXT>

