<F P=100> Vietnam </F>
<H3> <TI>   Foreign Embassies To Issue Visas Directly </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK2302155294 Hanoi VNA in English 1521 GMT 23 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> BK2302155294 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi VNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Hanoi VNA Feb. 23 -- As of February 15 this year 
foreign embassies in Vietnam are able to issue directly visas 
for Vietnamese people who go abroad to do official business. 
  The Consulate Department under the Ministry for Foreign 
Affairs will continue to be responsible for arranging visas for 
high-level party, National Assembly and government delegations 
which go abroad to do official business. 
  For other delegations and individuals after the issue of 
passports the Foreign Ministry will grant notes and introduction 
papers for specialized cadres of the offices and institutions in 
charge or representative of the delegation going abroad so that 
they come to foreign embassies to apply for a visa. 

</TEXT>

