<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The inspector general of police, Tan Sri Rahim Noor, 
has admitted that it is difficult for the police to obtain 
information on allegations that the opposition in Malaysia were 
receiving money from the Australian Secret Intelligence Service, 
ASIS. He said this was expected since no one would in his right 
mind admit being involved in espionage. He disclosed this to 
reporters after the breaking of fast at the Police Training 
Center in Kuala Lumpur last night. However, Tan Sri Rahim said 
police would continue with investigation into the allegations. 
Prime Minister Datuk Sri Dr. Mahathir Mohamed was also present 
at the function attended by some 1,000 police personnel of all 
ranks. 

