<H3> <TI>   MNDP Discusses `Present' National Situation </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW2202171494 Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME in English 1455 GMT 22 Feb 
94 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW2202171494 </F>
<F P=104>  Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Ulaanbaatar, February 22 (OANA-MONTSAME) -- The 
General Council of the National Democratic Party of Mongolia 
(MNDP) has discussed at its sitting the present situation 
created in the country and has drawn a conclusion that the MNDP 
can not participate in work of the State Great Hural (SGH), 
preserving its party representative in the parliament the MNDP 
considers that the supreme legislative organ of the country the 
State Great Hural failed to be an organ of political pluralism 
and in consequence of this the meaning of a democratic state 
system is being lost, the main provisions of the Constitution 
are being violated, but the MNDP has not adopted a final 
decision on the issue of recalling their representatives in the 
parliament. 

