<H3> <TI>   `Coalition of the Four Unions' Discuss Corruption </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW2202171394 Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME in English 1453 GMT 22 Feb 
94 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW2202171394 </F>
<F P=104>  Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Ulaanbaatar, February 22 (OANA-MONTSAME) -- The 
leaders of "the coalition of the four unions" organized in the 
middle of the last year (the Mongolian Democratic Union, the New 
Progressive Union, the Union of Mongolian Youth Organizations, 
the Union of Mongolian Students) have met here to exchange views 
and discuss the situation in the country created in connection 
with the scandal about involvement of the leaders of the 
parliament and the government in corruption. 
  According the results of the meeting it was decided to 
resume 
activity, coordinate their further actions with the coalition of 
the Mongolian National Democratic Party and the Mongolian Social 
Democratic Party. 

