<F P=100> Indonesia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Committee: 15,000 Register for Bosnia Fight </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2302102994 Belgrade VECERNJE NOVOSTI in Serbo-Croatian 19 
Feb 94 p 4 </F>

<F P=103> AU2302102994 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade VECERNJE NOVOSTI </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> ["M.S."-initialled report: "15,000 Mercenaries Arriving"] </F>
  [Text] The Indonesian committee for helping Bosnian 
Muslims has announced that at least 15,000 young men had 
reported to leave for Bosnia. 
  Ahmed Sumarugono [name as published], deputy chairman of 
this 
committee, said, according to a report in the Istanbul newspaper 
GUNAYDIN, that about 50,000 voluntaries will be registered by 
the end of the week, after which the Indonesian Army will be 
asked to train all those people who have registered to leave for 
Bosnia in handling arms and in other military skills as soon as 
possible. 

</TEXT>

