<DATE1>  25 Feb 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> Indonesia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Suharto Reaffirms Intention To Complete Term </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK2402082494 Jakarta ANTARA in English 0636 GMT 24 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> BK2402082494 </F>
<F P=104>  Jakarta ANTARA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Jakarta, Feb 24 (ANTARA) -- President Suharto 
said Thursday he would continue to fulfil his constitutional 
obligations given by the People's Consultative Assembly (MPR) as 
its mandatory [mandate holder] for the 1993-98 presidential 
tenure. "I will fulfil my constitutional duties," the president 
was quoted as saying by Religious Minister Tarmizi Taher. 
  The head of state made the remarks in response to questions 
of a number of ulemas put forward by the minister on the 
implementation of his task as the MPR mandatory. Tarmizi Taher 
said that a number of ulemas raised concern that Suharto would 
leave his post before his tenure is completed in 1998. The 
minister said he had received a number of telephone calls from 
ulemas asking clarification on rumors that President Suharto 
will leave his post before completing his presidential tenure. 
He said that the telephone on this question also came from the 
Indonesian Ulemas Council's (MUI) Chairman Hasan Basri. 
  On the occasion, the minister also reported on his recent 
visit to Saudi Arabia to observe preparations for the 1994 
pilgrimange season. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

